      <title>Northern Canada Needs a Diesel Diet</title>
      <category domain="https://www.newsdeeply.com/arctic/environment/">Environment</category>
      <pubDate>Mon, 28 Dec 2015 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <author>Chris Windeyer</author>
      <link>https://www.newsdeeply.com/arctic/articles/2015/12/28/northern-canada-needs-a-diesel-diet</link>
      <guid>https://www.newsdeeply.com/arctic/articles/2015/12/28/northern-canada-needs-a-diesel-diet</guid>
      <description>Much of the Canadian Arctic is still powered by old, diesel-fired power plants. In Nunavut, the reliance on diesel is total, and in the Northwest Territories it’s a drain on government funds. In both places, a post-carbon economy is for now a distant fantasy.</description>
